pageContext.description: Edge damaged by use. Sandy humus closely compacted in socket of celt.
pageContext.patina: deep brown patina with a bright apple green patina in patches
pageContext.surface: surfaces are lustrous & the metal is in a perfect state
pageContext.publications: Will be described in Pt. III Vol. III "Proceedings Prehistoric Society"
pageContext.collection: Private Collection, A.L. Armstrong Esq. 14 Swaledale Rd, Sheffield.
pageContext.site: England, Norfolk, Weeting, Grimes Graves (pit No1.), 10th Sept. 1920., found by owner at bottom of pit (opened by prehistoric Soc. of E. Anglia) having fallen therein through destruction of pit sides by frost & rain, from the surface layer of humus & sand.
